          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation, study, and recitation and is a kind of medieval Hindu philosophical treatise written in the style of a late Vedic upaniṣad, but is part of a likely medieval group of 108 so-called Yoga upaniṣads, which were influenced by both Saṃkhyā and Vedānta schools of philosophy as well as Śaktaism.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
